<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <title>SPINSPOT</title>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.1.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
  <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.1.3/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>
</head>
<body>

<div class="container-fluid p-3 bg-dark text-white text-center">
  <h1>SPINSPOT</h1>
  <h2>Exposing Bias in News Reporting</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="container-fluid p-4 bg-secondary text-black">
  <h4>
  In an age of information overload, it's getting harder to trust the news. ANY news.<br>

  A story breaking halfway around the world passes through reporters, editors,
  network executives, CEOs and other stakeholders before it ever reaches your eyeballs.<br>

  We may never know the whole truth, but learning to spot the motives behind
  the way a story is told can help us to get closer to it.<br>

  We're not saying one news outlet is "better" or "worse" than any other. That's
  for you to decide.<br>
  SPINSPOT is here for one thing: To show the differences in reporting, empowering readers to make up their own mind about the news.<br><br>
  </h4>
  </div>
    <div class="container-fluid p-2 bg-secondary text-black">
      <h2>How it Works</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Search for a current story or issue, or select one from our suggestions.</li>
        <li>We'll show you a headline and @articles summary from three different news sources.</li>
        <li>Compare and contrast. Critique and criticize.</li>
        <li>Develop your VERY OWN informed opinion on any issue, AND be able to back it up!</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  <div class="container-fluid p-1 bg-dark text-white text-center">
    <h2>Here's a sample:</h2>
    <h1>Recent Stories on <%= @name.titleize %></h1>
<div class="container xl-5 ms-auto">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-sm-4 p-2 ms-auto" style="background-color:#969696">
      <h3><%= link_to image_tag(@articles[0].photo_url, alt: "#{@articles[0].side}-image", height: 200),
      @articles[0].url if @articles[0].photo_url %></h3>
      <h4><%= link_to @articles[0].title, @articles[0].url, class: "link-dark text-decoration-none" %></h4>
      <p><%= @articles[0].summary %></p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-sm-4 p-2 ms-auto" style="background-color:#6b6b6b;">
      <h3><%= link_to image_tag(@articles[1].photo_url, alt: "#{@articles[1].side}-image", height: 200),
      @articles[1].url if @articles[1].photo_url %></h3>
      <h4><%= link_to @articles[1].title, @articles[1].url, class: "link-dark text-decoration-none" %></h4>
      <p><%= @articles[1].summary %></p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-sm-4 p-2 ms-auto" style="background-color:#969696">
      <h3><%= link_to image_tag(@articles[2].photo_url, alt: "#{@articles[2].side}-image", height: 200),
      @articles[2].url if @articles[2].photo_url %></h3>
      <h4><%= link_to @articles[2].title, @articles[2].url, class: "link-dark text-decoration-none" %></h4>
      <p><%= @articles[2].summary %></p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
